\
<!-- The estuarine realm is one of the most threatened in South Africa, in terms of both number of ecosystem types and by area.  -->


## Ecosystem threat status assessment

\

About 59% of the 22 estuary types are threatened with 23% Critically Endangered, 18% Endangered and 18% Vulnerable. Of total estuarine area, 99% is threatened with 1% Critically Endangered, 57% Endangered and 41% Vulnerable.

Multiple interventions are required to avoid further decline in health. These include protection of freshwater inflow to estuaries and the sea, restoration of water quality, reduction in fishing effort and avoidance of mining, infrastructure development and crops in the estuarine functional zone.



